HEADWORD: Phonographer
<hw>Pho*nog"ra*pher</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One versed or skilled in phonography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who uses, or is skilled in the use of, the
phonograph. See <er>Phonograph</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phonographical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Phonographic</ent>⟦br⟧
